Macao Foreign Trade Keeps Declining
MACAO , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Both exports and imports declined in Macao during the first 10 months of this year , according to figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department on Monday .
The figures indicated that exports from January to October were 14 billion patacas ( 1.75 billion U.S. dollars ) , down 1.3 percent from the same period last year .
Meanwhile , imports reached 12.9 billion patacas , decreasing 6.3 percent .
Despite shrinking exports and imports , trade surplus in the 10 months topped 1.1 billion patacas , skyrocketing 187 percent over the same months of last year .
In comparison with the same month of 1997 , exports and imports in October this year went down 2.9 percent and 5.1 percent respectively , resulting in a trade surplus of 114 million patacas .
Textiles and garments remained the leading exports of Macao , accounting for 84.3 percent of all exported goods from January to October this year .
Most of the exports were shipped to the United States and the European Union .
Most imports came from the Asian-Pacific region , including China 's mainland and Hong Kong , which supplied 56 percent of the goods .
